urlText: Trackwork may affect your travel
content:
Saturday 1 February
From 2am until 10pm
  • Trains run to a changed timetable and stopping pattern.
  • Revesby trains run to a changed timetable between Leppington and Central, platform 23, via the Airport. Some early morning trains run via Sydenham.
  • Most trains from Macarthur to the City run via Sydenham. Some early morning trains run via the Airport. Trains from the City to Macarthur run via the Airport.
  • You may need to change trains at Revesby if travelling to Airport stations.

  • Buses replace trains between Macarthur and Glenfield, then continue to Fairfield.

content:
On Saturday 1 February bus services will divert due to road closures for the Sun Run event.

From 6am until 11.15am route 136 services between Freshwater and Manly will travel via Pittwater Rd in both directions missing stops along North and South Steyne and Queenscliff Rd Manly; and The Strand and Griffin Rd in Dee Why. urlText: Trackwork between Glenfield and Fairfield
content:
Saturday 1 February
From 2am until 10pm
  • Buses replace trains between Glenfield and Fairfield.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Fairfield and Central, platforms 1-12. Most trains will not stop at Ashfield.
  • Trains also run between Leppington and the City via the T8 Airport & South Line.
From 10pm until 2am
  • Buses replace trains between Leppington, Liverpool and Fairfield.
  • Buses also replace T8 Airport & South Line trains between Macarthur, Glenfield and East Hills.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Fairfield and Central, and also between East Hills and Central.
